WEBVTT

1
00:00:00.000 --> 00:00:02.680
Hey, it's me, Andrea again.

2
00:00:02.960 --> 00:00:04.960
Let's keep building on where we left off.

3
00:00:05.180 --> 00:00:11.060
In this module, we're covering the mindset
behind every call 10 principles that'll shape

4
00:00:11.060 --> 00:00:15.300
how you think and how you sound before you
ever pick up the phone.

5
00:00:16.980 --> 00:00:23.140
Before you dial a single number, it's
crucial to have the right mindset locked in.

6
00:00:23.620 --> 00:00:25.660
Your job is not to be the buyer.

7
00:00:25.980 --> 00:00:27.860
Your job is to be the guide.

8
00:00:29.320 --> 00:00:34.560
When you stop trying to win the property and
start focusing on winning clarity for the

9
00:00:34.560 --> 00:00:37.340
seller, the whole dynamic shifts.

10
00:00:38.000 --> 00:00:39.420
You are not here to pitch.

11
00:00:39.780 --> 00:00:41.280
You are here to diagnose.

12
00:00:43.380 --> 00:00:45.720
Think of it like walking into a doctor's
office.

13
00:00:46.880 --> 00:00:51.480
The doctor does not start by measuring the
cabinets or asking the age of the water

14
00:00:51.480 --> 00:00:55.560
heater. They start with, what seems to be
the problem today?

15
00:00:55.640 --> 00:01:00.208
That is how you need to open every
conversation. Lead with their problem, not the

16
00:01:00.208 --> 00:01:01.700
property specs.

17
00:01:02.240 --> 00:01:05.740
That is how you earn trust and get to real
motivation fast.

18
00:01:07.720 --> 00:01:14.200
There are 10 principles that will shape how
you think and how you sound on every call.

19
00:01:15.820 --> 00:01:17.720
First, service over self.

20
00:01:18.220 --> 00:01:23.652
You assume you will help this person even if
you are not the solution. Picture a seller

21
00:01:23.652 --> 00:01:26.740
who inherited a house two states away.

22
00:01:27.100 --> 00:01:29.880
She is a not looking for the highest price.

23
00:01:30.380 --> 00:01:33.160
She is looking for someone who will make it
simple.

24
00:01:33.500 --> 00:01:38.820
The moment you stop chasing the deal and
start solving her problem, she stops guarding

25
00:01:38.820 --> 00:01:45.180
and starts talking. That attitude disarms
defenses and unlocks creativity in ways that

26
00:01:45.180 --> 00:01:46.320
pressure never will.

27
00:01:48.420 --> 00:01:52.180
Second, alignment. Get on their side of the
table.

28
00:01:52.600 --> 00:01:54.460
See the world through their lens.

29
00:01:56.360 --> 00:02:00.940
A landlord who has been dealing with the
same problem tenant for two years is not

30
00:02:00.940 --> 00:02:05.100
thinking about ARV. He is thinking about
getting his life back.

31
00:02:05.320 --> 00:02:10.260
When you acknowledge that before you talk
numbers, you are usually the first person who

32
00:02:10.260 --> 00:02:14.600
actually heard him. That is when
conversations turn into deals.

33
00:02:16.700 --> 00:02:19.260
Third, clarity beats pressure.

34
00:02:19.980 --> 00:02:24.300
Most sellers are frozen because they cannot
picture the goal post.

35
00:02:24.900 --> 00:02:29.540
A seller who says, I just need to think
about it is usually not stalling.

36
00:02:30.020 --> 00:02:32.460
They are scared because the path forward is
blurry.

37
00:02:33.880 --> 00:02:38.800
Your job is to help them write the movie by
starting at the end.

38
00:02:39.320 --> 00:02:41.260
Where are you living after closing?

39
00:02:41.880 --> 00:02:43.660
How much cash is in your pocket?

40
00:02:44.080 --> 00:02:49.640
When they can see it, they can move toward
it and deals become natural next steps

41
00:02:49.640 --> 00:02:51.300
instead of hard closes.

42
00:02:53.280 --> 00:02:57.960
Fourth, detach from outcomes and attach to
actions.

43
00:02:58.820 --> 00:03:01.100
You cannot control what a seller decides.

44
00:03:01.660 --> 00:03:05.280
You can control reps, tone, and follow-up
cadence.

45
00:03:05.800 --> 00:03:11.640
Think about this. Most deals in this business
come from the third, fourth, or fifth

46
00:03:11.640 --> 00:03:12.440
follow-up.

47
00:03:12.440 --> 00:03:18.580
The rep who stays consistent and never
sounds desperate is the one who wins.

48
00:03:19.240 --> 00:03:22.680
If you do not feel needy, you will not sound
needy.

49
00:03:24.840 --> 00:03:27.520
Fifth, curiosity over cleverness.

50
00:03:28.120 --> 00:03:29.880
You do not need to be interesting.

51
00:03:30.580 --> 00:03:32.340
You need to be interested.

52
00:03:33.160 --> 00:03:36.720
Ask simple, direct questions and then shut
up.

53
00:03:36.880 --> 00:03:40.680
A seller will tell you the real reason they
are selling if you give them room.

54
00:03:40.680 --> 00:03:45.280
Most people never get that room because the
person on the other end keeps filling the

55
00:03:45.280 --> 00:03:47.780
silence. Do not be that person.

56
00:03:48.260 --> 00:03:49.880
Ask the question and wait.

57
00:03:51.640 --> 00:03:57.020
Sixth, equal status. You are not beneath
them begging and you are not above them

58
00:03:57.020 --> 00:03:59.680
lecturing. Peer-to-peer energy.

59
00:04:00.400 --> 00:04:04.560
If a number does not work, say it plainly
and keep rapport intact.

60
00:04:04.900 --> 00:04:07.260
Sellers respect directness.

61
00:04:07.680 --> 00:04:11.680
What they cannot stand is someone who feels
either desperate or dismissive.

62
00:04:13.180 --> 00:04:16.020
Seventh, long game wins.

63
00:04:16.680 --> 00:04:18.380
You do not overcome people.

64
00:04:18.840 --> 00:04:20.400
You outlast confusion.

65
00:04:21.240 --> 00:04:26.360
A seller who says no in week one might be
ready in week six after they realize the

66
00:04:26.360 --> 00:04:28.860
certainty you offered was the real value.

67
00:04:28.860 --> 00:04:35.080
Follow up with warmth, bring a new angle
each time, and let time mature motivation.

68
00:04:35.780 --> 00:04:39.540
Most high-priced sellers are just early in
their decision curve.

69
00:04:41.700 --> 00:04:43.580
Eighth, problems are puzzles.

70
00:04:44.300 --> 00:04:47.520
Every objection is a missing piece, not a
wall.

71
00:04:48.100 --> 00:04:53.020
When a seller says, I need more money, that
is an invitation to find out what the money

72
00:04:53.020 --> 00:04:55.260
is for. Is it to pay off a loan?

73
00:04:55.840 --> 00:05:01.540
Cover a move? Once you know what the money
actually needs to do, you can often find a

74
00:05:01.540 --> 00:05:04.760
way to solve it that has nothing to do with
raising your price.

75
00:05:06.420 --> 00:05:08.800
Ninth, reps create calm.

76
00:05:09.280 --> 00:05:13.000
Confidence comes from thousands of
conversations, not hype.

77
00:05:13.400 --> 00:05:17.240
Be willing to be bad on call one so you can
be great on call one thousand.

78
00:05:17.700 --> 00:05:20.440
Make the extra call, that is where your edge
builds.

79
00:05:21.960 --> 00:05:25.320
Tenth, alignment beats argument.

80
00:05:25.900 --> 00:05:30.640
When you see the world through their lens,
the conversation stops being a numbers fight.

81
00:05:31.140 --> 00:05:34.100
You are not trying to win, you are trying to
understand.

82
00:05:34.520 --> 00:05:36.240
That distinction is everything.

83
00:05:38.140 --> 00:05:41.460
Hold these ten principles before every
single dial.

84
00:05:41.660 --> 00:05:43.440
They are your operating system.

85
00:05:43.760 --> 00:05:46.500
If they are sloppy, every script glitches.

86
00:05:48.640 --> 00:05:51.100
Thank you for engaging with this module.

87
00:05:51.600 --> 00:05:55.680
I encourage you to revisit it frequently for
a recap of these ten principles.

88
00:05:56.260 --> 00:05:59.680
Take a moment to stand up, stretch, and
hydrate.

89
00:05:59.980 --> 00:06:02.500
I look forward to seeing you in the next
module.
